# Data Architecture 
Activity 1: A Data-Driven Workflow Approach
User (Employee/Requestor)
Submits a Network Request using Service Catalog
Service Catalog Item (sc_cat_item)
Captures request details → creates a Request (sc_request)
Requested Item (sc_req_item)
Each catalog item becomes a requested item
Approval (sysapproval_approver)
Manager/Network Admin approves the request
Task (sc_task)
Fulfillment task assigned to the Network Team

# Business Rules
Business Rules in ServiceNow were used to automate backend logic, such as auto-assigning tasks to the Network Support Group, 
updating request status after approvals, and sending notifications when tasks or requests are completed.

# Automation Logic
Description
The workflow automates the end-to-end process of network requests in ServiceNow. When a user submits a catalog item,
the system generates a request, routes it for approval, creates fulfillment tasks for the network team, and sends notifications at each stage until closure.



